TITLE:: ValueView
summary:: Create customizable UI views associated with values and assignable actions.
categories:: Undocumented classes
related:: Classes/ValueViewLayer, Classes/RotaryView, Classes/XYScaleView, Classes/ValuesView

DESCRIPTION::
Create customizable UI views associated with values and assignable actions.
A ValueView stores a value and will draw a representation of that value
in whatever way you choose, using Pen's drawing methods (ValueView uses a UserView
internally). The view automatically updates when the value is set, and the view can
optionally be made interactive to change the value as well as perform an action
when the value changes. Update rates can be limited and repeated actions can be
suppressed.

The class isn't quite plug-and-play â€” ValueView is meant to be subclassed to author a new
view/value representation, along with authoring ValueViewLayers which define drawing layers.
link::Classes/RotaryView:: offers a more elaborate example of how a value can be displayed
in various ways akin to a rotary encoder or "knob" control.

To represent more than one value associated in a single view, see link::Classes/ValuesView::.


